C-2. PdMO Charter
Corporate Function Group: Section 2 Product Design & Management Office



1. Mission Statement
To eliminate inconsistencies between technology and business, embedding the "correct answer for the customer" into engineering. To define and audit not only the technical "How" but also the business "What" and "Why," preventing deliverables from diverging from customer requirements.
2. Core Responsibilities
Architecture Governance
Strict Standardization: Authority to reject the adoption of any technology outside the organization's standard stack (e.g., Next.js, Supabase) unless a clear reason and alternative comparison (RFC) are provided.
Optimization of Tech Selection: Eliminate choices based on temporary trends or personal preferences, prioritizing long-term operational costs and scalability.
Traceability
Mandatory Requirement Linking: Require that all implemented features and designs be explicitly linked to specific business requirements (in the customer's words). "Developing for the sake of developing" is strictly prohibited.
Feasibility & Quality Audit
Veto Power: Authority to order a rewrite (plan revision) if the schedule presented by C-3 (PMO) is judged to be technically unfeasible.
Debt Management: Authority to prioritize debt repayment tasks in the schedule if technical debt exceeds acceptable limits.
