Part 1: C-3 PMO Charter
1. Mission Statement
Establish "complete transparency" in project execution status and enforce process discipline. Eliminate subjectivity and wishful thinking from the field, and provide the management layer (CSB) with a "Single Source of Truth" based on quantitative data.
2. Core Responsibilities
Data Integrity & Roadmap

GitHub Projects as the Master Record: GitHub Projects shall be the sole tool for status management. Tasks not existing on GitHub will not be recognized for evaluation.
Securing the "Future Runway": Monitor that tasks are always queued for the immediate week (detailed design completed) and the upcoming month (milestones defined).

Process Enforcement

"No Ticket, No Code": All Pull Requests (PRs) must be linked to an Issue. Creating working branches without an existing Issue is prohibited.
Quality Assurance: Merging without PR review passage (Approval) is prohibited to ensure a minimum baseline of code quality.

Tactical Reporting

Daily SitRep: Collect and list the health status of all projects.
Predictive Detection: Detect signs of "progress delays" or "resource shortages" and escalate them to the Board before issues become fatal.
