5. Criteria & Governance
The PMO shall audit projects using the following criteria. If criteria are not met, corrective actions must be taken.

Ticket Hygiene

Zero Overdue: Overdue tickets must always be zero.
No Stale Issues: Issues with no status movement for 3 days or more must be split or reported as blocked.

Planning Horizon

One Week Rule: Tickets to be started the following week must have specifications, assignees, and deadlines fully defined.
One Month Rule: Milestones and large-scale tickets (Epics) for one month out must be raised. Never create a state where there is "nothing to do tomorrow."

Traceability

Linkage: All PRs must be linked to an Issue. (Rogue commits without Issues are prohibited).
Review: All merged PRs must have an Approval log from someone other than the author.


